                            <comment id="13917714" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 3 Mar 2014 03:39:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10191&quot; title=&quot;Move large arena storage off heap&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-10191&quot;&gt;HBASE-10191&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mcorgan&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mcorgan&quot;&gt;Matt Corgan&lt;/a&gt; suggested the allocator could also do constant small (sequential) compactions. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can maintain new metrics on numbers of buffers allocated, stats on arenas, stats on wastage and internal fragmentation of the buffers, etc, and use these to guide additional optimizations and refinements.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14070404" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 22 Jul 2014 15:48:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-6709&quot; title=&quot;Implement off-heap data structures for NameNode and other HDFS memory optimization&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HDFS-6709&quot;&gt;HDFS-6709&lt;/a&gt; introduces a slab allocator as hadoop-common-project/hadoop-common/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/util/SlabAllocator.java . It&apos;s simple but can be easily adapted for this issue as a starting point for further refinements. The hadoop-common code introduces a SlabRegion type that is very similar to our PositionedByteRange.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
